The '''''Annals of Saudi Medicine''''' is a [[peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[medical journal]] published bimonthly by the [[King Faisal Specialist Hospital]] and Research Centre (Riyadh, Saudi Arabia). The journal publishes original articles, brief reports, case reports and letters. Other sections are editorials, special communications, perspectives, images,  "what’s your diagnosis" and commentary on published articles.

== History ==
The ''Annals of Saudi Medicine'' was established in 1981 as the ''King Faisal Specialist Hospital Medical Journal''. It obtained its current title in 1985. The ''Annals'' went from a quarterly to a bimonthly publication in 1988.

